  "explanation": "Use a min-priority queue of boundary cells. For each cell, explore neighbors. Water depth for neighbor is max(0, currentBoundaryMax - neighborHeight). Update neighbor with new boundaryMax and add to heap.",
  "answer": "def trapRainWater(heightMap):\n    if not heightMap: return 0\n    m, n = len(heightMap), len(heightMap[0]); h = []; visited = set(); res = 0\n    for i in range(m): \n        for j in [0, n-1]: heapq.heappush(h, (heightMap[i][j], i, j)); visited.add((i, j))\n    for j in range(1, n-1):\n        for i in [0, m-1]: heapq.heappush(h, (heightMap[i][j], i, j)); visited.add((i, j))\n    while h:\n        val, r, c = heapq.heappop(h)\n        for dr, dc in [(0,1),(0,-1),(1,0),(-1,0)]:\n            nr, nc = r+dr, c+dc\n            if 0<=nr<m and 0<=nc<n and (nr,nc) not in visited:\n                res += max(0, val - heightMap[nr][nc])\n                heapq.heappush(h, (max(val, heightMap[nr][nc]), nr, nc))\n                visited.add((nr, nc))\n    return res",
